<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="275" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="275">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="275">
<taxonomicName authority="Walckenaer, 1805" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Epeira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeira viridis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">Epeira viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Keyserling, 1865 was synonymised with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. transmarina" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" rank="species" species="transmarina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">H. transmarina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. by 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9661157" author="Dondale, CD" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" pagination="1157 - 1192" refId="B8" refString="Dondale, CD, 1966. The spider fauna (Araneida) of deciduous orchards in the Australian Capital Territory. Australian Journal of Zoology 14: 1157 - 1192, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9661157" title="The spider fauna (Araneida) of deciduous orchards in the Australian Capital Territory." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9661157" volume="14" year="1966">Dondale (1966)</bibRefCitation>
. This synonymy is rejected here in addition to other synonymies proposed by the author, including that of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. transmarina" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" rank="species" species="transmarina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">H. transmarina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. biapicata" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" rank="species" species="biapicata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">H. biapicata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="275">
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9661157" author="Dondale, CD" journalOrPublisher="Australian Journal of Zoology" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" pagination="1157 - 1192" refId="B8" refString="Dondale, CD, 1966. The spider fauna (Araneida) of deciduous orchards in the Australian Capital Territory. Australian Journal of Zoology 14: 1157 - 1192, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9661157" title="The spider fauna (Araneida) of deciduous orchards in the Australian Capital Territory." url="https://doi.org/10.1071/ZO9661157" volume="14" year="1966">Dondale (1966)</bibRefCitation>
considered a female lodged in the ZMH as holotype of 
<taxonomicName authority="Walckenaer, 1805" authorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="Epeira" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Epeira viridis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">Epeira viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Keyserling, 1865. This designation is here rejected as a female lodged in the NHM (NHM 1890.7.1.4237) much better matches the original description by 
<bibRefCitation author="Keyserling, E" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koeniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" pagination="799 - 856" refId="B21" refString="Keyserling, E, 1865. Beitraege zur Kenntniss der Orbitelae Latr. Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koeniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien 15: 799 - 856" title="Beitraege zur Kenntniss der Orbitelae Latr." volume="15" year="1865">Keyserling (1865)</bibRefCitation>
. This is also consistent with a comment by 
<bibRefCitation author="Rack, G" journalOrPublisher="Mitteilungen des Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museums und Instituts" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" pagination="1 - 60" refId="B36" refString="Rack, G, 1961. Die Entomologischen Sammlungen des Zoologischen Staatsinstituts und Zoologischen Museums Hamburg. II. Teil. Chelicerata II: Araneae. Mitteilungen des Hamburgischen Zoologischen Museums und Instituts 59: 1 - 60" title="Die Entomologischen Sammlungen des Zoologischen Staatsinstituts und Zoologischen Museums Hamburg. II. Teil. Chelicerata II: Araneae." volume="59" year="1961">Rack (1961</bibRefCitation>
, p. 25) who stated (from German) &quot; 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">
It is not clear if this is 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Keyserling’s">Keyserling's</normalizedToken>
type, as L. 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.121660" author="Koch, L" journalOrPublisher="Verhandlungen der Kaiserlich-Koeniglichen Zoologisch-Botanischen Gesellschaft in Wien" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" refId="B25" refString="Koch, L, 1871. Die Arachniden Australiens nach der Natur beschrieben und abgebildet. 1. Theil. 1. Lieferung. Verlag von Bauer und Raspe, Nuernberg, pg. 1-104, pl. 1-8. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.121660" title="Die Arachniden Australiens nach der Natur beschrieben und abgebildet. 1. Theil. 1. Lieferung. Verlag von Bauer und Raspe, Nuernberg, pg. 1 - 104, pl. 1 - 8." url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.121660" year="1871">Koch 1871</bibRefCitation>
, 84, also had specimens from Upolu
</emphasis>
&quot;.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="275">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1865" family="Araneidae" genus="Hortophora" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hortophora viridis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">Hortophora viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov. is much unlike 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" baseAuthorityYear="2021" class="Arachnida" family="Araneidae" genus="H." kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="H. transmarina" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" rank="species" species="transmarina">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">H. transmarina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov., specifically based on the shape and colouration of the abdomen and details of the epigyne (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 25" captionStartId="F25" captionText="Figure 25. Hortophora transmarina comb. nov., female (WAM T 84364). A. dorsal habitus; B. ventral habitus; C. epigyne, ventral view; D. epigyne, lateral view; E. epigyne, posterior view. Scale bars: 5 mm (A, B); 1 mm (C-E)." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606205" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">25A-C</figureCitation>
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">vs</emphasis>
Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 37" captionStartId="F37" captionText="Figure 37. Hortophora viridis comb. nov., holotype female from Upolu (Samoa) (NHM 1890.7.1.4237). A. dorsal habitus; B. ventral habitus." httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/606217" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">37A, B</figureCitation>
). The long epigyne is consistent with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" family="Araneidae" genus="Hortophora" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hortophora" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">Hortophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov. as diagnosed here and therefore the species is transferred to the genus, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Framenau &amp; Baptista &amp; Oliveira &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Keyserling" baseAuthorityYear="1865" family="Araneidae" genus="Hortophora" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hortophora viridis" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" rank="species" species="viridis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">Hortophora viridis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
comb. nov., pending an examination of males as part of a revision of Pacific 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Framenau &amp; Castanheira" authorityYear="2021" family="Araneidae" genus="Hortophora" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Hortophora" order="Araneae" pageId="0" pageNumber="275" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="275">Hortophora</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
gen. nov.
</paragraph>
